x + y = 100.
x = 2y.
 x + y = 2y + y = 3y = 100 \implies y = \frac{100}{3}, x = 2 \cdot \frac{100}{3}.
x + y + z = 100,
x = 2y, \\ y = 2z.
x = 2y = 2(2z) = 4z, \\ x + y + z = 4z + 2z + z = 7z = 100 \implies z = \frac{100}{7} = 14.\overline{285714}.
